wikipedia_page.main: Colonel Horace Hutton Barnet (6 March 1856 – 29 March 1941) was an English soldier and footballer.

response: * 6 March – Horace Barnet (d. 1941), England international in 1882 (one match); played for Royal Engineers.
* St. Thomas Orthodox Syrian Church - Consecrated on 8 February 1889 by then Bishop of Calcutta Ralph Johnson and built by Horace Barnet, the church, in 1897 was dedicated to Queen Victoria.
